"a.不正直的；弯曲的 【英】 adj.不正直的(not straight forward or frank)；弯曲的 (roundabout; winding) 【记】 de+vi(=via道路)+ous →离正道的→不正直的 【同】 n. deviousness 【例】 a devious person /a devious path adj. 不直接的; 步入歧途的; 迂回的 = roundabout = winding 【参】deviousness(n 不诚实 = dishonesty; 道路弯曲) 【记】源自deviate， vio 是via 的变体,来自于way路 【相关】obvious 明显的，pervious 能被通过的 devious (adj.)  1590s, ""out of the way,"" from Latin devius ""out of the way, remote, off the main road,"" from de via (see deviate). Originally in the Latin literal sense; figurative sense of ""deceitful"" is first recorded 1630s. Related: Deviously; deviousness. Figurative senses of the Latin word were ""retired, sequestered, wandering in the byways, foolish, inconsistent."""
